# Pull Request Rules

- PR descriptions must explain what changed and why it was changed.
- Include screenshots or recordings when the PR affects UI, layout, or visual behavior.
- Keep PRs focused so reviewers can understand and validate the change easily.
- Call out any notable risks, follow-up work, or areas that need extra reviewer attention.

## PR Must Include

- What was changed
- Why it was changed
- Screenshots if the PR includes UI changes

## Checklist Before Merging

- The PR title follows the project naming convention.
- The description is complete and reflects the actual change.
- Relevant tests were added or updated when needed.
- Existing tests pass or any known failures are clearly explained.
- Screenshots or recordings are attached for UI changes.
- Risks, limitations, and follow-up items are documented when applicable.

Example:

```text
PR must include:
- What was changed
- Why it was changed
- Screenshots (if UI)
```
